## New testable assertions added

A15 – SelectionProvider selection access is available (macro-safe)
A15.1 In WORK_ENV, com.nomagic.magicdraw.ui.SelectionProvider is resolvable and callable in the macro environment.
A15.2 In WORK_ENV, selection retrieval should not depend on com.nomagic.magicdraw.ui.SelectionManager (it may be missing or unnecessary).
A15.3 In WORK_ENV, SelectionProvider.getInstance(project).getMainElement() can be called without throwing, and may return null when nothing is selected.
A15.4 If the returned main element respondsTo("getElement"), calling getElement() should not throw; it may return the underlying model element.
A15.5 For elements that respondTo("getType"), calling getType() should not throw; when non-null it is the desired classifier-ish result for part properties and proxy ports.

